==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: assembly language
<hw>assembly language</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>an artificial computer language with
mnemonic codes representing the basic machine-language instructions of a
computer, which can be interpreted by an assembler to produce a computer
program in machine language. Also informally referred to as
<altname>assembler</altname>.</def> <note>Writing a program in assembly
language is very much simpler than writing the machine instructions in
binary code, and the use of such a language greatly increases the
efficiency of the process of writing computer programs. See also
<er>programming language</er>, <er>FORTRAN</er>,
<er>BASIC</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

